#compdef rumqttd
# Documentation: source-direct extraction from upstream
# bytebeamio/rumqtt rumqttd/src/main.rs clap-derive `CommandLine`
# struct + `Command::GenerateConfig` Subcommand variant.
# Reference accessed: 2026-05-30 via gh api.
# bytebeamio rumqttd R145b — high-performance MQTT broker in
# Rust from the bytebeamio team. Embeddable + lightweight; built
# on the rumqtt async MQTT client/broker family. Sister broker to
# the heavily-covered emqx / mosquitto family in the corpus.

_arguments -s -S \
  '(-c --config)'{-c+,--config=}'[path to config file (default: built-in rumqttd.toml)]:file:_files -g "*.toml"' \
  '*'{-v,--verbose}'[increase verbosity (stackable: -v info, -vv debug, -vvv trace)]' \
  '(-q --quiet)'{-q,--quiet}'[launch without printing banner]' \
  '--version[show version]' \
  '1:subcommand:((generate-config\:write-default-config-to-stdout))'
